com/amazons-palm-reading-tech-tested-panera-cafes-133037398.html">在 Panera 咖啡馆</a>享用早餐。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>手掌识别系统被认为比触碰支付和其他非接触式系统更具优势，这些系统仍然需要某种物理物品，包括亚马逊基于计算机视觉的<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-just-walk-out-tech-comes-to-two-whole-foods-stores-101036042.html">Just Walk Out</a>技术。它也可能对企业有所帮助。它确保酒精购买者达到法定年龄，并且扫描的更深层次性质（同时检查手掌和静脉）创建了一个独特的矢量“签名”，据称该矢量“签名”无法复制。</p><p>然而，这种方法也有其批评者。出于<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-one-palm-scanning-red-rocks-amphitheater-denver-arts-and-venues-153114212.html">隐私和人权考虑，</a>活动人士呼吁音乐场所和其他场所放弃亚马逊一号。尽管亚马逊宣传掌纹签名的安全云存储以及防篡改保护，但反对者担心政府可能会利用这些数据来追踪抗议者和边缘化人群。反对者还担心黑客仍然可能窃取和滥用数据。</p><p>该公司已经因其做法面临法律麻烦。一项拟议的集体诉讼指控<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-faces-lawsuit-over-alleged-biometric-tracking-at-go-stores-in-new-york-144429703.html">亚马逊未能明确通知 Go 商店购物者它正在收集包括手掌在内的生物识别数据，从而违反了纽约市法律</a>。亚马逊坚称 One 用户明确同意数据收集，但尚不清楚这是否足以遵守立法。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-bringing-its-palm-based- payments-to-all-whole-foods-market-stores-132413042.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-bringing-its-palm-based-payments-to-all-whole-foods-market-stores-132413042.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4c08e062-1d2e-4f43-819e-ae9078eda6c1</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 13:24:13 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689862326</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T14:12:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="2786" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/55f62